From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 12:14:40 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): journal snapshots + crash-safe compaction
 (FR-E83)

Add a `state_snapshot` journal event and a crash-safe compaction operation
(automatic in the engine, manual via CLI) that bounds journal.jsonl size and
replay cost without weakening the FR-E69 durability contract.

- run-journal.ts: extend the single replayer to seed from the LATEST snapshot
  (suffix-only end-scan; pre-snapshot lines never parsed), forward-refuse an
  unsupported snapshot_version (names path+version), keep torn-tail tolerance
  (incl. right after a snapshot), and track eventsSinceSnapshot; add
  buildStateSnapshotEvent. Snapshot-free journals replay unchanged.
- journal-compaction.ts (new): exact 5-step crash-safe protocol
  (replay -> tmp snapshot -> fsync -> copy .bak -> atomic rename) shared by
  engine + CLI; refuses a non-replayable journal; compactRun adds the active
  live-lock refusal; one .bak generation kept.
- engine: auto-compact at a node-completion (level) boundary, never mid-node,
  past defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events (default 1000, 0=off).
- config: validate the new non-negative-integer settings field.
- cli: `runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId> [--dry-run]` with the
  exact summary line; refusal/not-found exit non-zero one-line; in --help.
- docs: FR-E83 SRS section + index row; SDS journal/recovery notes.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
