+### 3.83 FR-E83: Journal Snapshots with Crash-Safe Compaction
+
+- **Description:** The append-only recovery journal (`journal.jsonl`, FR-E69)
+  supports **state snapshots** and a **crash-safe compaction** operation that
+  bounds journal size and replay cost without weakening the durability
+  contract.
+  - **Snapshot event:** a new journal event kind `state_snapshot` carrying
+    `snapshot_version: 1`, the complete replayed run model at that point
+    (everything replay reconstructs — run status/metadata, per-node
+    statuses/facts, declared nodes/directories, costs), and `events_covered`.
+  - **Replay from snapshot:** the single replayer in
+    `src/state/run-journal.ts` (no second replayer) seeds from the LATEST valid
+    snapshot and applies only the events after it. Replaying `snapshot + tail`
+    reconstructs a run model deeply-equal to replaying the full original
+    journal (equivalence invariant). Replay of a compacted journal is
+    suffix-only — pre-snapshot lines are never parsed. A snapshot whose
+    `snapshot_version` exceeds the supported version fails replay with an error
+    naming the journal path and version (forward refusal). Snapshot-free
+    journals replay byte-identically to before (backward compatible). Torn
+    trailing lines remain tolerated, including a torn line right after a
+    snapshot.
+  - **Compaction protocol (exact order):** (1) replay the current journal;
+    (2) write `journal.jsonl.tmp` = one `state_snapshot` + zero tail;
+    (3) fsync the tmp file; (4) copy the current journal to `journal.jsonl.bak`
+    (one generation kept); (5) atomically rename tmp over `journal.jsonl`. A
+    crash at any intermediate point leaves a journal that still replays.
+    Compaction refuses (clear error, nothing modified) when the run is active
+    (lock held by a live process) or the journal does not replay cleanly beyond
+    torn-line tolerance.
+  - **Engine integration:** settings-level field
+    `journal_compaction_threshold_events` (non-negative integer; `0` disables;
+    default `1000`). During a run the engine auto-compacts at node-completion
+    boundaries only (never mid-node) when events-since-last-snapshot exceeds the
+    threshold; the trigger is one verbose line.
+  - **CLI:** `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId>
+    [--dry-run]` performs manual compaction with the same protocol and refusal
+    rules; `--dry-run` reports counts/bytes and modifies nothing; success
+    prints exactly `compacted <runId>: <eventsBefore> -> <eventsAfter> events,
+    <bytesBefore> -> <bytesAfter> bytes (backup: journal.jsonl.bak)`;
+    not-found/refusal cases exit non-zero with a one-line error.
+- **Tasks:** [journal-snapshots-compaction](../tasks/2026/06/journal-snapshots-compaction.md)
+- **Motivation:** Long runs grow `journal.jsonl` unbounded and replay cost
+  grows with it (FR-E69 explicitly deferred snapshots/compaction to a future
+  task). Snapshots cap the replay prefix; the crash-safe protocol guarantees
+  recovery is never weaker than the append-only contract it replaces.
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - **Tests:** `src/state/journal-snapshot_test.ts` (round-trip equivalence,
+    latest-snapshot seeding, suffix-only replay, torn-line-after-snapshot,
+    forward refusal, backward compat); `src/state/journal-compaction_test.ts`
+    (crash injection between every protocol step, both refusal cases, one-gen
+    backup, dry-run no-op); `src/config/config_test.ts` (FR-E83 threshold
+    validation + drift); `src/engine/engine_test.ts` (boundary-only
+    auto-trigger; threshold `0` disables); `src/cli_test.ts` (`runs compact`
+    arg parsing + exact summary format). Evidence: `deno task check`.
