+# engine: Journal snapshots with crash-safe compaction
+
+## Goal
+
+Bound the size and replay cost of the per-run append-only `journal.jsonl`
+recovery contract by adding **state snapshots** to the journal format and a
+**crash-safe compaction** operation (automatic in the engine, manual via CLI)
+that truncates the replay prefix without ever weakening durability.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+`journal.jsonl` (FR-E69) is the single recovery surface for a run: an
+append-only JSONL stream replayed from an empty model into `RunState`. Long
+runs grow it without bound and replay cost grows linearly. The FR-E69 design
+explicitly deferred snapshots/compaction to "a future task that demonstrates a
+measured need" — this is that task.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` owns the **only** replayer
+  (`replayRunJournal` → `applyJournalEvents`) and the append writer
+  (`RunJournalWriter`). It tolerates duplicate `event_id`s and a torn final
+  line (truncated after a crash).
+- `src/types.ts` declares the journal event union (`RunJournalEvent`),
+  envelope (`RunJournalEventBase`), kinds (`RunJournalEventKind`), and
+  `RunJournalReplayResult`.
+- `src/engine/engine.ts` holds the live `RunJournalWriter` as `this.journal`
+  and appends lifecycle facts; node-completion boundary is the `executeNode`
+  success path.
+- `WorkflowDefaults` + `DEFAULT_WORKFLOW_DEFAULTS` + `validateSchema` defaults
+  block define/validate workflow-level settings; FR-E7 drift coverage lives in
+  `config_test.ts`.
+- CLI subcommands (`run`/`answer`/`init`/`mcp`) dispatch in `cli.ts`.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Single replayer: extend `run-journal.ts`; a second replayer is forbidden
+  (item 4).
+- Backward compatibility: snapshot-free journals replay byte-identically
+  (item 2).
+- No new dependencies; follow existing `cli.ts` arg-parsing style; reuse
+  existing path/state helpers (`getJournalPath`, `getRunDir`, `isRunLive`).
+- `deno task check` stays green. No compression, no multi-gen `.bak`, no
+  cross-run/batch compaction (out of scope).
+- Error handling: compaction must be crash-safe at every intermediate step;
+  refusals surface as clear one-line errors (no stack trace at the CLI),
+  nothing modified on refusal. Replay forward-refuses an unsupported
+  `snapshot_version` with a clear error naming the journal path + version.
+
