+## Solution
+
+### Selected Variant — Architecturally-correct (modular shared protocol)
+
+Extend the single replayer in `run-journal.ts`; put the crash-safe compaction
+protocol in a dedicated `src/state/journal-compaction.ts` module shared by
+engine and CLI; add the config field to `WorkflowDefaults`. Rationale recorded
+under "Variant Selection" below.
+
+### Files to Create or Modify
+
+- `src/types.ts`
+  - Add `"state_snapshot"` to `RunJournalEventKind`.
+  - Add `StateSnapshotJournalEvent { kind:"state_snapshot"; snapshot_version:number;
+    run_model: RunState; events_covered: number }` to the `RunJournalEvent` union.
+  - Add `journal_compaction_threshold_events?: number` to `WorkflowDefaults`
+    (JSDoc: non-negative int, 0 = disabled, default 1000).
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts`
+  - `SUPPORTED_SNAPSHOT_VERSION = 1`; export.
+  - `parseJournal`: locate the latest `state_snapshot` line by scanning from the
+    end (cheap substring pre-filter `"kind":"state_snapshot"` then confirm by
+    parsing only the candidate); parse forward only from that line. Pre-snapshot
+    lines are never `JSON.parse`d (suffix-only). Preserve torn-tail tolerance
+    (including a torn line right after the snapshot) and malformed-non-tail
+    throwing for the suffix. Forward-refuse `snapshot_version > SUPPORTED`
+    naming the journal path + version. Return added fields:
+    `eventsSinceSnapshot`, `replayedFromSnapshot`, `preSnapshotLinesSkipped`.
+  - `applyJournalEvents`: `case "state_snapshot"`: seed `state =
+    JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(event.run_model))` (byte-faithful), then apply
+    tail events on top.
+  - `RunJournalReplayResult` gains optional `replayed_from_snapshot`,
+    `pre_snapshot_lines_skipped` (additive; back-compat).
+  - `RunJournalWriter`: track `#eventsSinceSnapshot` (set at `open()` from
+    parse, incremented per `append()`); expose `eventsSinceSnapshot` getter.
+  - `buildStateSnapshotEvent(runId, seq, runModel, eventsCovered, ts?)` helper.
+- `src/state/journal-compaction.ts` (new)
+  - `compactJournal(runDir, { runId, dryRun?, faultHook? }) → CompactionSummary`
+    implementing the 5-step protocol exactly. Replay-clean refusal lives here
+    (shared). `faultHook(step)` is the test-only abort seam.
+  - `CompactionStep` enum for crash-injection points.
+- `src/state/lock.ts` — reuse `isRunLive` (no change) for the CLI active-lock
+  refusal wrapper.
+- `src/engine/engine.ts`
+  - After a top-level node completes (success path in `executeNode`), if
+    `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events > 0` and
+    `this.journal.eventsSinceSnapshot > threshold`: call `compactJournal`,
+    reopen `this.journal` (`RunJournalWriter.open` continues `seq`), emit one
+    verbose line via `this.output.status("engine", …)`.
+- `src/config/config.ts`
+  - Add `journal_compaction_threshold_events: 1000` to
+    `DEFAULT_WORKFLOW_DEFAULTS`; validate in `validateSchema` defaults block
+    (non-negative integer).
+- `src/cli.ts`
+  - `runs compact` subcommand: parse `--workflow`/`--run`/`--dry-run` in the
+    existing manual style; active-lock refusal via `isRunLive`; delegate to
+    `compactJournal`; print the EXACT summary line on success; one-line error +
+    non-zero exit on refusal/not-found; add to `--help`.
+- `src/mod.ts` — export `compactJournal`, snapshot type, `SUPPORTED_SNAPSHOT_VERSION`.
+- Tests — colocated: `journal-snapshot_test.ts`, `journal-compaction_test.ts`
+  (state), `config_test.ts` (config), `cli_test.ts` (CLI), `engine_test.ts`
+  (auto-trigger).
+- Docs — FR-E83 SRS section (01-execution-model) + index row
+  (requirements-engine.md) + SDS journal/recovery note
+  (design-engine/04-data-and-logic.md); `types.ts` JSDoc.
+
+### Compaction protocol (exact order, item 9)
+
+1. Replay current `journal.jsonl` (refuse if it does not replay cleanly beyond
+   torn-tail tolerance — nothing modified).
+2. Write `journal.jsonl.tmp` = one `state_snapshot` event (seq = maxSeq+1,
+   `events_covered` = events replayed) + zero tail.
+3. `fsync` the tmp file.
+4. Copy current `journal.jsonl` → `journal.jsonl.bak` (one generation).
+5. Atomically rename tmp over `journal.jsonl`.
+
+Only `journal.jsonl` is consulted by replay and it is replaced atomically at
+the final step, so a crash at any boundary leaves it replayable (old content
+until step 5, new content after).
+
+### Error handling strategy
+
+- Forward refusal: `snapshot_version > 1` throws
+  `Unsupported snapshot_version <v> in <path> (supported: 1)`.
+- Compaction refusals throw plain `Error`; CLI catches → one-line `Error: …`,
+  exit 1 (no stack). Active-lock refusal checked at the CLI boundary (engine
+  auto-compaction holds its own lock and must not self-refuse).
+- Auto-compaction failures: surface (fail-fast), do not silently swallow.
+
+### Verification Commands
+
+- `deno task check`
+- `deno test -A --no-check src/state/ src/config/ src/engine/engine_test.ts src/cli_test.ts`
+
+## Variant Selection
+
+- **Quick fix** (inline snapshot + compaction in `run-journal.ts`/`cli.ts`):
+  fastest, but buries a heavily-tested crash-safe protocol in the writer module
+  and couples CLI/engine to it ad hoc. Cons: poor testability of crash
+  injection, scope creep in `run-journal.ts`.
+- **Architecturally-correct** (SELECTED): extend the one replayer; isolate the
+  crash-safe protocol in `journal-compaction.ts` shared by engine + CLI; config
+  field on `WorkflowDefaults`. Pros: honors item 4 (single replayer) and the
+  "shared by engine and CLI" mandate (item 9); clean crash-injection seam;
+  minimal blast radius. Cons: one new module + type surface.
+- **Best long-term** (pluggable checkpoint/policy framework, version-migration
+  layer): explicitly out of scope — task scopes out multi-gen retention,
+  compression, batch compaction, and only `snapshot_version: 1` exists.
+  Over-engineering.
+
+Chosen: **Architecturally-correct** — it is the smallest design that satisfies
+every hard requirement (single replayer, shared crash-safe protocol, crash
+injection, refusals, config drift, CLI contract) without over-building beyond
+the stated scope.
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- (deferred) Snapshot-version migration framework if a `snapshot_version: 2`
+  is ever needed — out of scope now.
