+ * the same protocol as engine auto-compaction. Refuses (exit 1, one-line
+ * error, nothing modified) when the run is active or the journal does not
+ * replay cleanly. `--dry-run` reports event counts / byte sizes and modifies
+ * nothing — and skips the active-lock refusal since it cannot corrupt a live
+ * run. On success prints exactly the canonical summary line.
+ */
